abstract: CHICAGO, May 12 -- Wheat -- The trade opened to-day with the same feeling of depression and discouragement that was so prominent yesterday. The only demand came from shorts, and they were not eager to buy, while the selling was general and was mostly of long wheat. To the bulls the outlook appears very gloomy. There was not an argument to-day which could by any means be twisted into favoring better prices.
